news.title: I-T dept raids Hotel Royal Plaza's chairman for stashing Rs 40 crore abroad
news.para: "Foreign Asset Investigation Units (FAIUs) of Income Tax department has conducted this search for undisclosed assets held by Mittal abroad and possessing black money in foreign shores," the I-T officials told adding that "in this regard 18 premises across Delhi, Mumbai and Daman were covered during the search operation."

news.title: Chandigarh: Special committee recommended for need-based changes in properties
news.para: On the pattern of Chandigarh Housing Board (CHB), MP Kirron Kher-led committee has recommended a special committee for need-based changes in properties under the estate office.The 11-member committee, headed by Kher, was formed on the directions of Supreme Court.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board demolishes illegal constructions in Sector 56
news.para: The board is computing the cost of demolitions which will be recovered from the allottees. In case of non-payment, their allotments could be cancelled.

news.title: Chennai Metro to lease out 2.11 lakh sq ft space at Shenoy Nagar
news.para: Officials said the underground complex built over a 4.3lakh sqft area will have a 2.1lakh sqft shopping space and 1.7lakh sqft parking area for 404 cars and 893 bikes.

news.title: Indore administration expects to earn Rs 350 crore from selling three government assets
news.para: According to senior administrative officials, as many as three properties owned by different departments of the MP Government, have been listed on MP Public Assets Management Department’s portal for auction.

news.title: Manesar: Raheja Navodaya RWA fined Rs 1 lakh for defunct sewage treatment plant
news.para: In February this year, MCM imposed a penalty of Rs 1 lakh, however at that time the STP was being operated by the builder. In April, the RWA took over the operations and maintenance of the STP but has failed to ensure environmental norms are followed.

news.title: Haryana: New policy on handover of upkeep, RWAs not enthused
news.para: The draft policy addresses the formation of the AOA, its functioning, and upkeep of common areas, and elaborates on the role of promoters vis-à-vis individual allottees and RWAs.

news.title: Mumbai: Vision Crest residents oppose BMC's nod for 12 flats in refuge area
news.para: Officials said the plot could be developed with a much higher FSI as the Mahim coast was declared a bay in 2014 by the state coastal authority, after the Centre’s 2011 notification, amending CRZ norms.

news.title: MahaRERA asks landowner to finish abandoned Palghar project
news.para: ​​The builder had completed just 20% work on site. An association of allottees of the project requested MahaRERA to replace the builder and allow the landowner to complete the project.

news.title: Mukesh Gandhi buys duplex for over Rs 50-crore in Mumbai's Khar
news.para: Gandhi continues to be a key shareholder of Angel One, the listed company of Angel Broking, holding nearly 6% stake in the company. The deal values the apartment spread over 5,555 sq ft at over ₹90,000 per sq ft.

news.title: Toppr.com founder buys property in Bandra for Rs 41 crore
news.para: The luxurious real estate project has a total super-built-up area of more than 50,000 sq ft, consisting of a basement, ground floor, and six podium parking spaces. There are eight habitable floors in the project out of a total of 15.

news.title: All kinds of property numbers should be cross-referenced, put up on dashboard: Karnataka HC
news.para: ​This order came in a petition where a builder tried to "take advantage of certain lacunae in the manner and methodology of numbering". A fine of Rs 1 lakh was imposed on Vandana Infra Estates which had filed the petition.

news.title: China Evergrande's CEO, CFO step down after probe into property services unit
news.para: The indebted company was investigating how deposits worth 13.4 billion yuan ($1.99 billion) belonging to the unit, Evergrande Property Services, were used as collateral for pledge guarantees and seized by banks.

news.title: Schindler cuts revenue guidance for 2022 on China slowdown
news.para: CEO Silvio Napoli said on a conference call that China's market could contract by 15% to 30% this year. China accounted for around 18% of Schindler's sales last year.

news.title: Pune: Seven housing societies fined for not processing waste at source
news.para: As per the guidelines, housing societies or commercial establishments generating more than 100kg of garbage, categorized as bulk waste generators, should process the wet waste on their premises.
